## Solution Narrative

### Current Status
The VA Health & Benefits mobile app is growing, but there is not yet a single documented IA framework that clearly defines where features should live or what qualifies for Home screen placement. This creates ambiguity for teams and risks making the Home screen less intentional over time.

This epic defines the shared criteria, hierarchy, and app-level placement model needed to support consistent decision-making now and as the app continues to expand.

### Key Decisions

- The Home screen should be treated as intentional, high-value real estate rather than a catch-all surface
- Not all features belong on the Home screen, and explicit exclusion guidance is necessary
- Feature placement should be governed by shared app-level IA buckets rather than one-off decisions
- Existing app features should be reviewed and classified to establish a complete baseline
- The IA framework and related decisions should be documented in a reusable, shareable format for future teams

